This paper deals with visually grounded conversational agents, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which deals with CV. The paper also involves decision-making and machine learning techniques, which fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the potential for more efficient and natural interactions, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
